<subSubSection id="CFF1651AFFFD8131D7C4FD8B5544B194" pageId="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="87543691FFFD8131D7C4FD8B527BB00C" blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1219]" box="[151,636,582,607]" pageId="6">
Length. Male: 
<quantity id="40139B74FFFD8131D66EFD8B51B8B00D" box="[317,447,582,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.5mm</quantity>
; female: 
<quantity id="40139B74FFFD8131D575FD8A527FB00C" box="[550,632,583,607]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87543691FFFD8131D794FDA75166B140" blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1219]" pageId="6">
Greenish ochraceous (Plate 
<collectionCode id="E1FAAE54FFFD8131D551FDA6521EB0D1" box="[514,537,619,642]" pageId="6">II</collectionCode>
: A). Head broader than pronotum. Vertex centrally with black marking between anterior margins of eyes. Two black spots at posterior margin of vertex. Pronotum shiny, with black spots, laterally carinate. Scutellum dark brown with posterior margin yellowish. Ocelli at anterior margin (Plate 
<collectionCode id="E1FAAE54FFFD8131D21DFD7E5562B099" box="[1358,1381,691,714]" pageId="6">II</collectionCode>
: B). Frontoclypeus entirely black, anteclypeus black with yellow lateral margin (Plate 
<collectionCode id="E1FAAE54FFFD8131D36CFD1A5451B0BD" box="[1087,1110,727,750]" pageId="6">II</collectionCode>
: D). Forewing macropterous with brown veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87543691FFFD8131D794FCD35544B194" blockId="6.[151,1437,582,1219]" pageId="6">
<emphasis id="B59FEA83FFFD8131D794FCD3513BB164" bold="true" box="[199,316,798,823]" pageId="6">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with darkly sclerotized part on posteroventral margin more than its half, with sparse spinules, dorsoapical margin With 2–3 macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="1FD02A14FFFD8131D589FC8F533AB108" box="[730,829,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: A). Spinular dark serration present in a row near anal tube base. Connective Y-shaped with arms wide apart from each other (
<figureCitation id="1FD02A14FFFD8131D487FCAB543DB12C" box="[980,1082,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: C). Subgenital plate with 3–4 macrosetae, smaller than pygofer (
<figureCitation id="1FD02A14FFFD8131D578FC475295B1F0" box="[555,658,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: B). Style with well developed claw-like apophysis, inner process longer than outer process, wide apart (
<figureCitation id="1FD02A14FFFD8131D510FC6352A1B194" box="[579,678,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: D). Aedeagal shaft gently curved dorsally (
<figureCitation id="1FD02A14FFFD8131D3C7FC6354F0B194" box="[1172,1271,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1318,1340]" captionTargetBox="[180,1383,278,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,265,1296]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE5. Aconurellachoui sp. n. A. male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: connective, dorsal view; D: style, dorsal view; E: aedeagus, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, lateral view; G: valve, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1242517/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figure 5</figureCitation>
: E–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
